  "extras": {
    "summary": "AN ACT TO AMEND SECTION 75-24-15, MISSISSIPPI CODE OF 1972, TO REVISE THE PRIVATE CAUSE OF ACTION UNDER THE CONSUMER PROTECTION LAWS FOR AN INDIVIDUAL SUFFERING LOSS; TO REMOVE THE REQUIREMENT THAT A PLAINTIFF FIRST RESOLVE A DISPUTE IN AN INFORMAL DISPUTE SETTLEMENT PROGRAM; TO REQUIRE A PLAINTIFF TO NOTIFY THE ATTORNEY GENERAL OF AN ACTION WITHIN FOURTEEN CALENDAR DAYS OF FILING; TO AUTHORIZE THE ATTORNEY GENERAL TO JOIN THE SUIT; TO PROVIDE A VENUE FOR A PRIVATE ACTION BROUGHT UNDER THIS SECTION; TO AUTHORIZE INJUNCTION RELIEF; AND FOR RELATED PURPOSES."
  },
